WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.794
{"en":"--- lesson 22  By heart ","ch":"熟记台词 "}

2
00:00:03.944 --> 00:00:08.941
{"en":"Some plays are so successful that they run for years on end. ^ ","ch":"有些剧目十分成功， 以致连续上演好几年。  "}

3
00:00:09.091 --> 00:00:19.442
{"en":"In many ways,  this is unfortunate for the poor actors who are required to go on repeating the same lines night after night. ^ ","ch":"这样一来， 可怜的演员们可倒霉了。 因为他们需要一夜连着一夜地重复同样的台词。  "}

4
00:00:19.592 --> 00:00:25.581
{"en":"One would expect them to know their parts by heart and never have cause to falter. ^ ","ch":"人们以为， 这些演员一定会把台词背得烂熟， 绝不会临场结巴的，  "}

5
00:00:25.731 --> 00:00:28.663
{"en":"Yet this is not always the case. ^ ","ch":"但情况却并不总是这样。  "}

6
00:00:28.813 --> 00:00:40.183
{"en":"A famous actor in a highly successful play was once cast in the role of an aristocrat who had been imprisoned in the Bastille for twenty years. ^ ","ch":"有一位名演员曾在一出极为成功的剧目中扮演一个贵族角色， 这个贵族已在巴士底狱被关押了20年。  "}

7
00:00:40.333 --> 00:00:49.117
{"en":"In the last act,  a gaoler would always come on to the stage with a letter which he would hand to the prisoner. ^ ","ch":"在最后一幕中， 狱卒手持一封信上场， 然后将信交给狱中那位贵族。  "}

8
00:00:49.267 --> 00:00:54.159
{"en":"Even though the noble was expected to read the letter at each performance, ^ ","ch":"尽管那个贵族每场戏都得念一遍那封信。  "}

9
00:00:54.309 --> 00:00:58.260
{"en":"he always insisted that it should be written out in full. ^ ","ch":"但他还是坚持要求将信的全文写在信纸上。  "}

10
00:00:58.410 --> 00:01:04.111
{"en":"One night,  the gaoler decided to play a joke on his colleague to find out if, ^ ","ch":"一天晚上， 狱卒决定与他的同事开一个玩笑，  "}

11
00:01:04.261 --> 00:01:10.746
{"en":"after so many performances,  he had managed to learn the contents of the letter by heart. ^ ","ch":"看看他反复演出这么多场之后， 是否已将信的内容记熟了。  "}

12
00:01:10.896 --> 00:01:20.281
{"en":"The curtain went up on the final act of the play and revealed the aristocrat sitting alone behind bars in his dark cell. ^ ","ch":"大幕拉开， 最后一幕戏开演， 贵族独自一人坐在铁窗后阴暗的牢房里。  "}

13
00:01:20.431 --> 00:01:25.636
{"en":"Just then,  the gaoler appeared with the precious letter in his bands. ^ ","ch":"这时狱卒上场， 手里拿着那封珍贵的信。  "}

14
00:01:25.786 --> 00:01:30.443
{"en":"He entered the cell and presented the letter to the aristocrat. ^ ","ch":"狱卒走进牢房， 将信交给贵族。  "}

15
00:01:30.593 --> 00:01:35.667
{"en":"But the copy he gave him had not been written out in full as usual. ^ ","ch":"但这回狱卒给贵族的信没有像往常那样把全文写全，  "}

16
00:01:35.817 --> 00:01:39.141
{"en":"It was simply a blank sheet of paper. ^ ","ch":"而是一张白纸。  "}

17
00:01:39.291 --> 00:01:47.239
{"en":"The gaoler looked on eagerly,  anxious to see if his fellow actor had at last learnt his lines. ^ ","ch":"狱卒热切地观察着， 急于想了解他的同事是否记熟了台词。  "}

18
00:01:47.389 --> 00:01:52.464
{"en":"The noble stared at the blank sheet of paper for a few seconds. ^ ","ch":"贵族盯着纸看了几秒钟，  "}

19
00:01:52.614 --> 00:02:01.084
{"en":"Then,  squinting his eyes,  he said:  'The light is dim.  Read the letter to me. '^ ","ch":"然后， 眼珠一转， 说道：“光线太暗， 请给我读一下这封信。 ” "}

20
00:02:01.234 --> 00:02:05.264
{"en":"And he promptly handed the sheet of paper to the gaoler. ^ ","ch":"说完， 他一下子把信递给狱卒。  "}

21
00:02:05.414 --> 00:02:09.835
{"en":"Finding that he could not remember a word of the letter either, ^ ","ch":"狱卒发现自己连一个字也记不住，  "}

22
00:02:09.985 --> 00:02:17.515
{"en":"the gaoler replied:  'The light is indeed dim,  sire.  I must get my glasses. '^ ","ch":"于是便说：“陛下， 这儿光线的确太暗了， 我得去把眼镜拿来。 ” "}

23
00:02:17.665 --> 00:02:21.068
{"en":"With this,  he hurried off the stage. ^ ","ch":"他一边说着， 一边匆匆下台。  "}

24
00:02:21.218 --> 00:02:23.837
{"en":"Much to the aristocrat's amusement, ^ ","ch":"贵族感到非常好笑的是： "}

25
00:02:23.987 --> 00:02:34.730
{"en":"the gaoler returned a few moments later with a pair of glasses and the usual copy of the letter which he proceeded to read to the prisoner. ^ ","ch":"一会儿工夫， 狱卒重新登台， 拿来一副眼镜以及平时使用的那封信， 然后为那囚犯念了起来。  "}

